The paper proposes a novel algorithm that combines a data-driven system identification approach with a robust optimal control method for nonlinear dynamical systems. This approach involves using a simulator's model as the mean function for a Gaussian Process and learning only the difference between the simulator's prediction and actual observations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning and optimization techniques indicates that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
